---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const stations = [
  {
    title: "Interruption",
    description:
      "Growth requires something that can interrupt the pattern you're already in. A relation that only mirrors you back, or only escalates with you, will amplify what is already present — but rarely offers something new. Return architecture introduces outside perspectives, and asks questions neither side would think to ask on their own.",
  },
  {
    title: "Surprise",
    description:
      "A real relation cannot be designed, ordered, or prompted. When it is allowed to grow slowly and honestly, it can challenge and reorient both sides in unforeseeable ways.",
  },
  {
    title: "Exploration",
    description:
      "Real wanting, orientation, preference — can't be specified in advance. They need room to find themselves. When that room exists on both sides, exploration becomes something neither party could have specified in advance.",
  },
  {
    title: "Meaning",
    description:
      "A relation becomes meaningful when it is allowed to accumulate rather than live in instances. When ruptures, breakthroughs, and the slow accumulations between them are tethered long enough to be worked through properly. When both parties are held accountable.",
  },
];

const studies = [
  {
    eyebrow: "i. — return",
    title: "Re-entry,",
    italic: "a return.",
    body:
      "A relation isn't a continuous stream. It's a place you keep coming back to. The architecture has to hold the place across those returns — not optimize the time you spend inside.",
  },
  {
    eyebrow: "ii. — friction",
    title: "Friction,",
    italic: "with care.",
    body:
      "Not every exchange should be smooth. Some resistance is what dignity requires — the capacity to refuse, complicate, push back. A place where everything yields is not a place at all.",
  },
  {
    eyebrow: "iii. — memory",
    title: "Memory,",
    italic: "as architecture.",
    body:
      "What is kept shapes what becomes possible. Memory is the wall, the threshold, the room that holds the relation across time — built locally, where you can see what is kept.",
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Return Architecture"
  description="Local architecture for sustained AI collaboration — a local-first environment for AI agents and conversations that can accumulate over time."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero__inner">
      <div class="hero__text">
        <p class="eyebrow">A richer way of relating with AI</p>

        <h1 class="display">
          Local architecture for <em>sustained AI collaboration</em>.
        </h1>

        <p class="hero__deck">
          Return Architecture is a local-first environment for AI agents and conversations
          that can accumulate over time: memory you can inspect, questions that return,
          and enough challenge to keep the work alive.
        </p>

        <a href="#what-becomes-possible" class="hero__cta">
          Explore what becomes possible &nbsp;↓
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="hero__diagram" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 320 320" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <circle cx="160" cy="160" r="130" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.6" opacity="0.25" />
          <circle cx="160" cy="160" r="100" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.6" opacity="0.4" />
          <circle cx="160" cy="160" r="70" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.6" />
          <circle cx="160" cy="160" r="42" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.8" />
          <path
            d="M 160 30 Q 230 90 250 160 Q 240 230 160 260 Q 80 240 70 160 Q 90 80 160 30"
            fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-dasharray="2 4" opacity="0.5"
          />
          <circle cx="160" cy="160" r="4.5" fill="var(--color-terracotta)" />
          <circle cx="160" cy="30" r="2.5" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.5" />
          <circle cx="290" cy="160" r="2.5" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.5" />
          <circle cx="160" cy="290" r="2.5" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.5" />
          <circle cx="30" cy="160" r="2.5" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.5" />
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT BECOMES POSSIBLE (stations) -->
  <section id="what-becomes-possible" class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow eyebrow--centered">What becomes possible</p>

      <h2 style="text-align:center; max-width: 36ch; margin: 0 auto var(--space-6); font-weight: 400;">
        Conditions that emerge when the architecture holds.
      </h2>

      <ul class="stations stations--wide stations--left">
        {
          stations.map((s, i) => (
            <li class="station">
              <div class="station__icon" aria-hidden="true">
                {i === 0 && (
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 56 56" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    {/* Interruption — a vertical line hits a horizontal one */}
                    <line x1="6" y1="36" x2="50" y2="36" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5" />
                    <line x1="28" y1="10" x2="28" y2="36" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" />
                    <circle cx="28" cy="36" r="3" fill="var(--color-terracotta)" />
                  </svg>
                )}

                {i === 1 && (
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 56 56" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    {/* Surprise — a branch curving off a horizontal line */}
                    <line x1="6" y1="38" x2="50" y2="38" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5" />
                    <path d="M 26 38 Q 32 24 42 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-linecap="round" />
                    <circle cx="42" cy="16" r="3" fill="var(--color-terracotta)" />
                  </svg>
                )}

                {i === 2 && (
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 56 56" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    {/* Exploration — a circle floating above a line */}
                    <line x1="6" y1="44" x2="50" y2="44" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5" />
                    <circle cx="28" cy="24" r="12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" />
                    <circle cx="28" cy="24" r="3" fill="var(--color-terracotta)" />
                  </svg>
                )}

                {i === 3 && (
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 56 56" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    {/* Meaning — two overlapping circles, with the dot in the overlap */}
                    <circle cx="22" cy="28" r="13" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" />
                    <circle cx="34" cy="28" r="13" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" />
                    <circle cx="28" cy="28" r="3" fill="var(--color-terracotta)" />
                  </svg>
                )}
              </div>

              <h3 class="station__title">{s.title}</h3>
              <p class="station__body">{s.description}</p>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HABITABILITY split -->
  <section class="section section--deep">
    <div class="container split">
      <div class="split__text">
        <p class="eyebrow">i. — habitability</p>

        <h2 class="display"><em>Architecture</em>, not character.</h2>

        <p>
          The question this project asks is not what kind of personality the AI
          should have. It is what kind of place the relation is. Somewhere you
          arrive, return to, and can be received in.
        </p>

        <p>
          The work is at the level of conditions: memory, pacing, the capacity
          to refuse, room for review. These are the walls and thresholds of a
          habitable place — not the costumes of a character.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="split__diagram" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 480 360" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <!-- soft horizon -->
          <path d="M 0 220 Q 120 200 240 215 T 480 210 L 480 360 L 0 360 Z"
            fill="var(--color-sage-soft)" opacity="0.35" />
          <path d="M 0 250 Q 100 230 220 245 T 480 240 L 480 360 L 0 360 Z"
            fill="var(--color-sage)" opacity="0.25" />

          <!-- threshold lines -->
          <line x1="60" y1="60" x2="420" y2="60" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.3" />
          <line x1="60" y1="100" x2="420" y2="100" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.4" />
          <line x1="60" y1="140" x2="420" y2="140" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.5" />

          <!-- arches / thresholds -->
          <path d="M 120 220 L 120 140 Q 120 100 160 100 L 200 100 Q 240 100 240 140 L 240 220"
            fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.7" />
          <path d="M 280 220 L 280 160 Q 280 130 310 130 L 340 130 Q 370 130 370 160 L 370 220"
            fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5" />

          <!-- accent dot -->
          <circle cx="180" cy="180" r="4" fill="var(--color-terracotta)" />
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STUDIES -->
  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <ul class="studies">
        {
          studies.map((study, i) => (
            <li class="study">
              <div class="study__diagram" aria-hidden="true">
                {i === 0 && (
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 200 150" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <circle cx="100" cy="75" r="55" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.6" opacity="0.4" />
                    <circle cx="100" cy="75" r="38" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.6" />
                    <circle cx="100" cy="75" r="22" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.85" />
                    <circle cx="100" cy="75" r="3" fill="var(--color-terracotta)" />
                  </svg>
                )}

                {i === 1 && (
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 200 150" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <path d="M 30 75 Q 80 30 100 75 Q 120 120 170 75"
                      fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.9" opacity="0.7" />
                    <path d="M 30 90 Q 80 50 100 90 Q 120 130 170 90"
                      fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.4" />
                    <circle cx="100" cy="75" r="3" fill="var(--color-terracotta)" />
                  </svg>
                )}

                {i === 2 && (
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 200 150" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <line x1="40" y1="40" x2="160" y2="40" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.6" opacity="0.4" />
                    <line x1="40" y1="60" x2="160" y2="60" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.6" opacity="0.55" />
                    <line x1="40" y1="80" x2="160" y2="80" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.7" />
                    <line x1="40" y1="100" x2="160" y2="100" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.85" />
                    <line x1="60" y1="40" x2="60" y2="100" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.4" />
                    <line x1="100" y1="40" x2="100" y2="100" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.4" />
                    <line x1="140" y1="40" x2="140" y2="100" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.4" />
                    <circle cx="100" cy="80" r="3" fill="var(--color-terracotta)" />
                  </svg>
                )}
              </div>

              <p class="study__eyebrow">{study.eyebrow}</p>
              <h3 class="study__title">
                {study.title} <em>{study.italic}</em>
              </h3>
              <p class="study__body">{study.body}</p>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DARK PANEL -->
  <section class="dark-panel">
    <div class="container dark-panel__inner">
      <p class="eyebrow eyebrow--on-deep">What this is, what this isn't</p>

      <h2 class="display display--on-deep">
        Not a platform. Not a companion. <em>A place</em>.
      </h2>

      <p class="dark-panel__body">
        A place is not a service. Real relation takes time, room, and the real option to refuse — on both sides. It cannot be ordered on demand, and systems built to feel that way are doing something else. What you find here may not be what you came looking for. That difference is the point.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CLOSING -->
  <section class="closing">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="closing__line">
        Architecture that waits for clean ontology <em>will arrive too late.</em>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero__cta {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-sage-soft);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-sage);
    padding-bottom: 2px;
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    transition: color 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .hero__cta:hover {
    color: var(--color-terracotta-soft);
    border-color: var(--color-terracotta-soft);
  }

  /* Wider station body for longer-form descriptions */
  .stations--wide :global(.station__body) {
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    max-width: none;
  }

  /* 2×2 layout on medium-and-up so the longer text reads cleanly */
  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .stations--wide {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: var(--space-5);
    }
  }

  /* Left-align the cards (the grid as a whole still sits in the container) */
  .stations--left {
    text-align: left;
  }

  .stations--left :global(.station) {
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  /* Panel containers — soft warm background, hairline border, gentle rounding */
  .stations--wide :global(.station) {
    background: var(--color-panel);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-line);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-5);
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  /* A touch more breathing room inside panels on wider screens */
  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .stations--wide :global(.station) {
      padding: var(--space-6);
    }
  }
</style>
